  "prompt": "How do you solve a math problem?",
  "response": "To solve a math problem, you can follow these general steps:\n\n1. **Read the problem carefully**: Make sure you understand the question and what it is asking. Identify the key pieces of information and the unknowns.\n\n2. **Identify the type of problem**: Determine whether it is an arithmetic, algebraic, geometric, or some other type of problem. This will help you decide on the appropriate method to solve it.\n\n3. **Choose a strategy**: Depending on the type of problem, you can choose a strategy such as drawing a diagram, setting up an equation, or using a specific formula.\n\n4. **Apply the strategy**: Use your chosen strategy to solve the problem. Make sure to show your work and keep track of your steps.\n\n5. **Check your answer**: Once you have an answer, double-check your work to make sure it is correct. You can do this by plugging your answer back into the original problem or by using a different method to solve it.\n\n6. **Interpret the results**: Finally, make sure your answer makes sense in the context of the problem. If it doesn't, re-evaluate your work and try again.\n\nRemember, practice makes perfect, so the more you practice solving math problems, the better you will become at it.",
